    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The main reason why #2835 was not resolved is because it's unclear which decision we should take, if we load all pages, you could break an implementation, simply by putting a really big page number. The best solution likely is allowing pagination also to \"navigate back\", or to put a limit on \"preloaded pages\". \r\n\r\nFor now this is not a feature `connectInfiniteHits` has unfortunately ",
